node.text: Zara Rutherford is a 19-year-old aviator who is attempting to become the youngest woman to fly solo around the world and is a true inspiration. During a stopover in the BVI, I invited Zara to lunch and heard some wonderful stories about her journey. Very proud to see our wonderful people at @virgin supporting her endeavours, and showing young people everywhere how exciting a career in STEM can be! ✈️ @fly.zolo @holly_branson

node.text:
More than ever, we need new perspectives, different ideas and broader ways of thinking to solve the big problems of our time. 
 
This is where a neurodiverse workforce can really benefit a business. Many companies have caught on to the value of inclusion, but there are still lots of opportunities for thinking bigger and embracing different ways of thinking. 
 
It’s the reason we proudly support auticon, a majority-autistic technology consulting firm, that employs over 200 autistic adults. Read their Global Impact Report and find out how employment can help benefit the lives of adults with #autism #linkinbio
